name: Arcane Hood
lore: A pointed hat worn daily by Mages, wide and comfortable but sometimes obstructs vision.

name: Cursed Helmet
lore: A helmet worn by evil Warlocks, their faces obscured in shadow and darkness.

name: Flamelord's Helmet
lore: The king's gaze from the helmet sends shivers down the enemy's spine.

name: Paladin's Helmet
lore: A helmet worn by noble White Knights, its exquisite design is like a work of art.

name: Ranger's Feathered Hat
lore: It is both a tool to block the wind and his secret weapon to maintain his elegance!

name: Sage's Crown
lore: A crown made of branches, worn by the sages of the forest to signify their friendship with the woods.

name: Valiant Helmet
lore: A helmet worn by the brave Gladiator, covering the entire face.

name: Hero's Helmet
lore: A helmet of elegant craftsmanship. It is meticulously cleaned by heroes after each and every hour.

name: Knight's Helmet
lore: Well-crafted helmet, protects the head without obstructing vision.

name: Mercenary's Hood
lore: Unremarkable Hat, muffles noise but offers no protection from damage.

name: Traveler's Hat
lore: Traveler's Hat, shields from sunlight and blocks sandstorms.

name: Arcane Robe
lore: A robe often worn by Mages, said to be imbued with many spells.

name: Cursed Robe
lore: A robe worn by evil Warlocks are shrouded in ominous shadows.

name: Dragon Hunter Armor
lore: Crafted from the remains of a dead Wyrm, worn by dragonslayers who traverse the Phantasia Mountain to hunt mighty beasts.

name: Flamelord's Armor
lore: The wrath of a king burns like fire, destined to consume all.

name: Night Owl Armor
lore: Armor worn by thieves who dwell in darkness, blending perfectly into the night.

name: Paladin's Armor
lore: Armor worn by noble White Knights, its pure color signifies a pure soul.

name: Quenched Armor
lore: A sturdy set of armor forged by dwarfs under divine command, tailored for Paladins.

name: Ranger's Leather Armor
lore: A leather coat once worn by a forest ranger, believed to be hand-stitched by the wearer himself.

name: Valiant Armor
lore: Armor worn by valiant Gladiators, overprotective designs may sacrifice visual speed.

name: Hero's Armor
lore: A beautifully decorated armor that balances function and aesthetics.

name: Knight's Armor
lore: A cherished suit of armor, often worn by knights throughout their lives.

name: Mercenary's Leather Armor
lore: A plain leather coat that keeps you unnoticed, even by thieves and bandits.

name: Traveler's Leather Armor
lore: A soft leather coat, travelers value lightness over protection.

name: Arcane Gauntlets
lore: Mages sometimes wield their staffs in close combat, and thus wear gauntlets for protection.

name: Cursed Gauntlets
lore: Gauntlets worn by evil Warlocks, used to cast many vicious dark spells.

name: Dragon Hunter Gauntlets
lore: Gauntlets forged in the likeness of dragon claws, the claws of Wyrms outmatch all divine weapons.

name: Flamelord's Gauntlets
lore: For a king, gauntlets are not for protection, but for drawing the sword.

name: Night Owl Gauntlets
lore: A blackened gauntlet emerging from the shadows — a nightmare for many.

name: Paladin's Gauntlets
lore: White Knights once swore an oath: the sword gripped by these gauntlets shall never strike the weak.

name: Quenched Gauntlets
lore: It's said that if stained with the blood of the innocent, their shine will fade.

name: Ranger's Gloves
lore: Worn by forest rangers, these gloves protect the hands that draw the bowstring.

name: Sage's Gloves
lore: Even with gloves on, forest sages will gently caress the flowers.

name: Valiant Vambraces
lore: Gauntlets worn by brave Gladiators, only removed upon victory.

name: Hero's Gauntlets
lore: Exquisitely crafted gauntlets that need to be handled with care, repairs don't come cheap.

name: Knight's Gauntlets
lore: Tightly fitted gauntlets that offer solid protection for the hands.

name: Mercenary's Gauntlets
lore: Non-slip gauntlets that provide a better grip on sword hilts.

name: Traveler's Bracers
lore: Simply decorated bracers. Try blocking a blade with them, though they won't be much use.

name: Arcane Boots
lore: Mages often enchant their boots with acceleration spells, enjoying wind-like speed.

name: Dragon Hunter Boots
lore: Before the Wyrm falls a dragonslayer's footsteps never cease.

name: Night Owl Boots
lore: These boots move through the darkness without a sound.

name: Pious Boots
lore: Priests wear boots to tread through thorns and swamps to reach the sick.

name: Quenched Boots
lore: Paladins stand tall upon the earth, vowing to tread out every injustice beneath their feet.

name: Ranger's Boots
lore: Boots worn by forest rangers, ornate in appearance but remarkably light.

name: Sage's Boots
lore: When the Forest Sages walk through the woods, birds follow them in song.

name: Valiant Boots
lore: Boots worn by valiant Gladiators, gilded as a symbol of their victories.

name: Hero's Boots
lore: Heavy-soled boots, each step of the heroes echoes like thunder to their enemies.

name: Knight's Boots
lore: Boots crafted for knights, greatly reducing the chance of falling from horseback.

name: Mercenary's Boots
lore: Lightweight boots, making long-distance running no longer a dream.

name: Traveler's Boots
lore: Simple cloth boots that won't let you walk on water, but will get you through the desert.

name: Bloodseeker Sword
lore: Within its bloodlit blade dwell the souls of the dead, touch it and you'll hear their wails.

name: Curseblade
lore: When this curbed blade is drawn, curses follow like shadows.

name: Dragon Hunter's Greatbow
lore: It's said the mightiest dragonslayers can shoot an arrow through a dragon's skull. Stories like this may be legends, but legends often stem from truth.

name: Dragonslayer Greatsword
lore: This colossal object is less of a sword and more like a weapon carved from a massive chunk of iron, resembling a sword in shape!

name: Flamelord's Sword
lore: Strength is the mark of a king.

name: Gate of Truth
lore: What did he see behind that shattered stone gate? — Emptiness, wisdom, the ultimate truth of the universe.

name: Infinite Holy Sword
lore: The gods bless every warrior who wields this sword for justice, granting them infinite courage.

name: Invincible Meow-Meow Fist
lore: This is the Invincible Meow, soft and harmlesss on the outside, cunning and vicious within! When a Meow goes full firepower, can humans still resist?

name: Last Whisper
lore: A weapon favored by angels, said its arrows fly as fast as light.

name: Mana's Tide
lore: Sometimes as calm as calm as a deep spring, other times raging like a flood. Whoever can master the tides can wield magic power deeper than the ocean.

name: Phantom Blade
lore: Assassins believe that once these twin daggers are raised, the target is already as good as dead.

name: Quenched Warblade
lore: Once raised, it cannot be put down, except in death.

name: Requiem
lore: The golden arrow engraved with a scarab is symbol of life in the otherworldly realm.

name: Sage's Staff
lore: A staff made from the oldest branches in the forest, cherished by forest sages.

name: Ship Slayer
lore: It's said that when this hammer first emerged, the sky shifted and stars dimmed. Its power could split galaxies and shatter the stars.

name: Silver Sword of Demon Hunting
lore: Whoever holds this sword must have the courage to cleave through the darkness.

name: Song of Plenty
lore: No one has ever seen the strings of that harp, yet the artist claims he plays the melody of the four seasons. Before his death, he was taken to the radiant Valhalla to compose for the gods.

name: Sword of the Overlord
lore: Long ago, a king wielded this sword and conquered the world.

name: Tome of Stars
lore: The moment the page turns, an unrecognizable flood of color surges toward the sky, leaving only unreadable blankness behind.

name: Touch of the Undying Flame
lore: A staff burning with nether-blue flame, used by liches to curse their enemies.

name: Typhon's Wrath
lore: As the giant axe swings, thunder roars and flames surge. Like the claw of Typhon, it rends the earth and opens the abyss.

name: Hero's Blade
lore: Taste the wrath of my Holy Slash!.

name: Knight's Greatsword
lore: A huge, clumsy iron sword. Wielding one in each hand looks cool, but know your limits.

name: Mercenary's Shortsword
lore: A small-sized sword, not suitable for large prey.

name: Traveler's Longsword
lore: A plain wooden sword, useful against Slimes, but difficult against Goblins.

name: Ancient Dragon Scale
lore: Its teeth are Sharp Blades, its wings are hurricanes. In the near-eternal life of the Wyrm, only this reverse scale remains an untouchable sanctuary.

name: Blessing of the Sacred Tree
lore: Connecting past, present, and future — the root of Yggdrasil binds the Nine Realms. Even a single strand, given freely, is enough to upload a new world.

name: Bountiful Bouquet
lore: With the rhythm of the wind, blossoms stop the sacred tree release their fragrance, carrying harvest blessings across the Nine Realms.

name: Box of Pain
lore: Use fear as the base, add some screams and tears... Let it ferment in the Magic Box for seven days to yield a truly one-of-a-king soul.

name: Brave's Medal
lore: Through the gem at the pendant's center, one sees their younger self, brimming with hope and courage.

name: Dragonblood Seal
lore: A maple leaf picked by the Dragonslayer before departure, stained with dragon blood over the years. Its crimson hue has turned nearly black.

name: Dragonslayer's Guide
lore: In the ink-stained Dragonslayer's Journal, a bold line stands out: "To save the world, first slay your inner dragon."

name: Eagle Warrior Portrait
lore: Through the weathered statue of the Eagle Warrior Portrait, the soaring eagle of light and the warrior battling an evil dragon slowly align. Gaze upon it to gain boundless courage.

name: Flamelord's Proof
lore: A symbol of royal status, none may wear it but the king.

name: Magic Mirror of the Soul
lore: Legend says this magic mirror reveals the true form of all evil. A Dragonslayer once looked into it, only to see his own reflection.

name: Mana's Tear
lore: Tears engraved the ocean's memory. This long-lost treasure, sunken deep beneath the waves, will one day shine with undying brilliance.

name: Moonlight Flask
lore: When the sun sets, the moonlight will guide your way around.

name: Overlord's Proof
lore: Devour flesh and blood to pave the king's path, sacrifice souls to forge the pinnacle of glory.

name: Quenched Medal
lore: A Paladin once sacrificed his life to protect this medal.

name: Sage's Bracelet
lore: It is rumored that this bracelet can command Ancient Tree Guardians, though its truth remains unknown.

name: Spirit Turtle Talisman
lore: The impenetrable shell of the Dragon Turtle. No one had ever seen the creature itself. They say it's... extremely shy.

name: Starlight Magisterium
lore: An indescribable color that transcends all, twisting, flickering, shifting. Its endless magic has dyed the stardust iridescent.

name: Thorns of Rejection
lore: Souls abandoned and hurt, burning with vengeance, yet all they weave is a lonely thorn-wrought defense.

name: Truth Seeker's Emblem
lore: Silence signifies the wisdom of the sage: In the half-closed compass, the needle of truth always points to the unresolved.

name: Watcher's Magic Eye
lore: Don't move. It's watching you.

name: Wolf's Will
lore: No matter how cunning, no creature escapes the gaze of the wolf. Note that the badge's detection is not always reliable.

name: Hero's Medal
lore: This is the glory of immortality!

name: Knight's Bracelet
lore: When you need to prove your identity, present this bracelet.

name: Mercenary's Pocket Watch
lore: If you're running late, just check this to see the time.

name: Traveler's Canteen
lore: When you're lost in the desert, you'll be grateful you had this.
